em where you can spent points into mental, telekinetic or heat control. After maximizing mental control for example it is possible to let some bystander to attack to the target.So Lucius II is a bugfested sandbox which still is a good game even with its quirks. I hate to see a lot of the potential  gone waste for the broken AI, but it is good to notice that the game was develeoped with a tiny independent company with limited resources.I recommend to give this a try especially if you were fan of the first game. For newcomers I'd rather start with the first game merely for the story, which is pretty good. Or even better - buy the inexpensive bundle."
