,Recommended,296830,28200185,"Posted: 5 December, 2016",all,ozzyoscy,"I've learned reviews aren't always accurate.Reviews here made it sound like this is just a mindless sandbox where you're put in a town and just kill everyone, and that the only way to really kill people is with poisoned doughnuts. I've discovered this is inaccurate.It's the same game as Lucius 1 with a bit more freedom, which has its pros and cons. The first game gave you the whole mansion to explore, and on each level you had to kill a certain person a certain way. Now you're put in certain areas, still have certain objectives or have to kill certain people, but are free to kill everyone else in the area too and in any way you wish.There are numerous creative ways to kill people, with some set up for you to figure out the chain of events that could lead to a glorious/hilarious multi-kill. Poisoned doughnuts are just the last resort if you can't see or think of any other good way. I haven't encountered another game yet that lets you kill someone via forced anal entry with a certain sex toy shot from a pressure valve.The people are stupid, but that's part of the appeal. The game is intentional-unintentional ludicrous dark comedy. It's supposed be fun, and it would be a bad game and unfitting if you had to hardcore stealth through the whole thing like Splinter Cell or Metal Gear. Who stealths riding a tricycle and blowing someone's head clean off with a flying gas canister, I mean really?It can be a bit rough around the edges, a bit buggy every now and then, they need to work on that for the possible sequel. But I found myself spending ages in the first few levels just discovering all the crazy ways to murder people, and the game ended before it really got repetitive. No regrets."
