76561198135068854,Recommended,296830,15543649,"Posted: 25 April, 2015",all,Willcraft,"I honestly enjoy it more than the original Lucius. Sure the voice acting isn't as good, sure there are bugs, but the good stuff is just so good.While the cutscenes in the first game are satisfying, getting to plan your own murders is a ton of fun. It also gives the game more replay value than its predecessor, since in that one it kind of loses its touch once you know how to beat every stage. I also adore the new skill tree system and the abilities to choose from. Especially since it doesn't force you to specialize yourself; as long as you kill enough people in every stage, you can probably max out the skill tree. And still, it sure is fun to play through the game with different play styles. Wanna start off as a mind controlling puppetmaster? Do that! Wanna become a master of telekinesis and toss people around? Do that! Wanna watch stuff burn? Do that!Even though the game still steers your actions through the objectives, it still allows great freedom. Personally I'd love to see some kind of sandbox mode where you can choose between different locations to wreak havoc upon. The graphics have improved as well, so now I can finally look at Lucius's face without wanting to return to staring at the back of his head. The climax was also more impressive this time. It didn't just make you feel like an epic badass, it made you feel like an epic badass fighting a stronger epic badass. And that was fun.Which leads me to one of my few complaints (spoiler alert): I'm not a fan of Isaac. Mostly because of his voice. A character like him who appears to be obsessed with the prophecy and talks the way he does should have a psychotic kid voice to go with that. But instead he was given a really ordinary low-pitched evil voice. Same with the devil. What was wrong with his old voice? I really liked that one.But overall it's a really fun game, expecially if you like to get creative and watch people die. Don't expect to get ""Lucius, but even more"" because you won't. This game is very different from the previous one, and to me in a good way.I really, really hope they make a third game. And if that isn't enough to finish the storyline, a fourth. And a fifth. And a sixth. And as many as the developers deem neccessary. If they keep this up, I promise I will continue playing them."
