76561198086571183,Recommended,296830,14609863,"Posted: 23 February, 2015",all,Piquerist,"Spoilers ahoy.Okay, this is something that's bothered me with a lot of the down votes. They marketed it as a sandbox, there was never any doubt of what it was going to be. That's how it was always marketted, I didn't even really expect there to be a story to it, from what people were saying before it was released.Aside from that, there is actually a decent story, if you're paying attention. Having played this game more times than what would probably be considered healthy since it's release, I've had time to really pay attention to the story. Instead of the long cut scenes from the first movie, you have people talking about incidents that happened. You have newspaper clippings. You have things that are actually subtle, that you have to pick up on. It's not an overly cinematic game.Now, the game itself is buggy, more so than Lucius was, yes, but there's no game breaking bugs, really. Something might come up every now and again where you'll have to go back to the beginning of a level and play it over again, but other than that, I, personally, have not encountered any game breakers. I've never crashed playing this game or anything like that.And yes, the way the AI acts when you kill something is goofy. It's amusing to me. I enjoy it. But that's me.In short, yes, it's a buggy indie game. I didn't go into the game thinking there wasn't going to be bugs, because honestly, the first Lucius also had bugs, and there were some actual game breaking bugs in the first one.And there are a lot of references in the game that had me amused. Ludlow, for one. The younglings for another. Just small things they slipped into the game."
