76561198046939286,Recommended,296830,14676979,"Posted: 27 February, 2015",all,Valdurska,"Lucius 2, sequel to Lucius.In this game, you control Lucius, the son of the Devil. Your objective is to go around and kill people, for the glory of Satan of course. You're meant to use your environment as a tool to kill nurses, patients and other people. When you kill someone, you need to hide the bodies. Otherwise people will find them and grow suspicious and panicky.Now, as a game, the concept is very creative and fun. Who does not want to go around and use the supernatural to kill your foes? However the game seems to fall a bit on the matter of actual functionality. The game is riddled with bugs and glitches. For example, people in the game can sometimes glitch into the walls if you drag their bodies, the game can crash when you finish a level, and different sounds can go off without any particular reason. I had the music sound, which plays when you kill someone, play on a loop randomly, even if I was just standing still. Occasionally the narration would replay without a reason.Now, would I recommend the game? Yes. Even with the bugs, the game is actually rather fun and enjoyable. The puzzles are rather creative and when you figure them out, you actually feel pretty good about yourself.However, if you really cannot stand bugs and glitches in games, you may want to wait until the devs release a bugfixing patch. Lucius 2 really could use one."
