,Not Recommended,296830,34533839,Posted: 27 August,all,Daggsy,"TL;DR: gay.I don't mean that as in ""This is a bad game, it's so gay"" (although it IS a bad game), I mean it in a ""You'll probably enjoy this game more if you are a fan of male genitalia"".But... let's start with the animated cutscenes. I'm still not sure if the voice acting and animation is being intentionally bad for comedic effect, or if it is genuinely just poorly done. The sense of humour is kind of odd in this one, so it could be either to be honest. The voice acting is played straight and seems to want to be serious, but this is countered with craft paper-esque animation (complete with South Park Canadian jaw movements).It's a Unity game, so you know what to expect graphics-wise. Fine, but nothing special. Of course, this also brings oddness like people walking through doors, putting arms into walls in the non-animated cutscenes, bodies spazzing out on death and shooting into the air, items clipping out of reach into walls...Gameplay is like a watered down version of the early Hitman games. There are a variety of ways to kill people, which is actually pretty fun in itself, but absolutely no challenge at all. In fact, most of the time once you have the mind control skill (which you can unlock almost immediately), you may just find yourself starting a fire and marching people one by one into it and fuelling it to put the next one in until the level is empty. Stealth is virtually non-existent, anyone catching you in a 'restricted area' will briefly march after you and get bored almost immediately afterwards. There seems to be no real reason to 'hide' bodies as people will 'Panic' but not really do anything in particular other than run around.There are a lot of naked men in this game (whether this is a pro or a con is really down to you).Once you get into the more open areas later on in the game things feel somewhat more interesting, as the first chapter gets a bit samey after a while.No spoilers, but the ending literally just dumps you in an area where you have to go to the menu to quit out of it, which is an odd design choice. Seems... amateurish?The only way this is similar to the first game is the creativity of the deaths you can arrange. Lucius 1 was flawed, but it was better than this.I've went with ""Not recommended"" as I'd have wanted to go with a neutral and 'Recommended"" is too generous."
