76561198194062673,Recommended,296830,24556123,"Posted: 27 July, 2016",all,Alpha011,"I don't understand why so many people hate this game. I watched some let's play videos of this game and knew exactly what I was getting into. Yes the game has a few glitches (I had a floating man on the last level) and yes the story was a little lack luster but I felt that came from the narrators voice. So dull sounding and monotone.The gameplay however I felt was fun! It was a kill fest compared to the 1st game but this is Lucius 2, the boys powers are evolving so it would only make sense his mischievous murders would increase in number. Why waste his effort killing one person at a time? Many more ways to kill people and it actually makes you think. Combine certain items to create a bomb or a lethal weapon, not really a checklist of what you have to do to specifically kill an NPC. The choice is up to you.TLDR:All in all I enjoyed the game. Gameplay was fun and exploring the areas was different. Story was a little dull due to voice acting. There are some really weird glitches. Seriously, I once had an NPC burn to death and his burned body began to stand up and walk around in a circle where he died... messed up."
