76561198064826014,Recommended,296830,34990507,Posted: 16 September,all,Prezi2,"I honestly don't know what the negative reviews are for...I picked this game up for $2.99 and given that, it was worth the money. It doesn't play like an early access game, it just plays like a indie game made by a small developer, and that's actually what it is. The level design in the hospitals is simplistic and repetitive but as you progress through the game, the ways that you can kill get more creative and inventive. There are times in this game where glitches and lag get frustrating. When someone is panicking, and you kill them, their panic timer will still continue even when they're dead...TLDR; Honestly, there isn't much to complain about, it's $2.99, made by a small indie developer and it's decent enough. Buy it."
