76561197968073802,Recommended,296830,35367940,Posted: 1 October,all,[LR] Laffi,"Before reading this review: Everything written under here is true, and I mean what I said. After restarting the game again, I had much more fun, because I knew the mechanics. I originally put this review as ""did not like the game/does not recommend"", but I want to change that to recommending it, but only for players who will play it more than once.This game probably had alot of ambitions to become a great game, but there are some things that ruins the entire experience. First of all. I did like this game in some sort of way after getting to understand how things worked, but I think that is the problem with the game in the first place.Starting the game, everything is really messed up, because you don't really know what you can do or not. I  realised that getting more skills, by KILLING PEOPLE, makes the game easier to progress in. My biggest problem was simply that it was hard to get people killed in the cool ways, because somehow it didn't always work. I wanted to blow someone up, I wanted to set someone on fire, or make em slip and fall on the floor, but it was complicated...I started killing everyone from level 3 and on, where I actually found ways to get it done, but it was alot of running around...and in the end most of them just got burnt in a fire. Shame that, because I bet there were so many other cool ways to kill em.As I said things doesn't always work properly, and the controls were extremely weird at the very last level. Things that worked before, didn't work then, and there was only one way to do complete it.The game got so much to offer, but I just think it there is absolutly something wrong with it. When I played the first game, you only got to kill one person per ""level"", but at least you had control over what was going on most of the time.So to sum up. Mechanics ruin the game, and it can be hard for someone that plays it the first time to understand.To end this review. I have no problem playing this game again, and I think the achievements are really cool. It makes it worth playing it more. I think that anyone that played this game for the 2nd time would have alot more fun than the first itme.Edit: I did and finished all achievements."
